<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="226" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1374,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1482,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is taken from Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rodrigues" authorityYear="2017" box="[806,895,1482,1507]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Chrosiothes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorus">
<emphasis box="[806,895,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">decorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(beautiful), in reference to the habitus of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1374,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1554,1579]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Females are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gertsch, 1936)" authorityName="Gertsch" authorityYear="1936" baseAuthorityName="Gertsch" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[703,1055,1554,1579]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Chrosiothes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minusculus">
<emphasis box="[703,865,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">C. minusculus</emphasis>
(Gertsch, 1936)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Levi" box="[1120,1241,1554,1579]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" refString="Levi, H. W. (1954) Spiders of the new genus Theridiotis (Araneae: Theridiidae). Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, 73, 177 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3223754" type="journal article" year="1954">Levi 1954</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 28, 29) by having the epigynum with a subcircular depression and by the shape of the internal genitalia with oval spermathecae, but differ by the subcircular depression farther from the posterior margin of epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1380,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[162,1394,340,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1416,323,1258]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrosiothes decorus new species: Female: 13, Epigynum, ventral, 14, Internal genitalia, dorsal, clarified. Chrosiothes una new species: Female: 15, Epigynum, ventral. Scale bars, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002470/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) and by the spermathecae more separated from each other (
<figureCitation box="[756,840,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[162,1394,340,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1416,323,1258]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrosiothes decorus new species: Female: 13, Epigynum, ventral, 14, Internal genitalia, dorsal, clarified. Chrosiothes una new species: Female: 15, Epigynum, ventral. Scale bars, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002470/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Males remain unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="7" pageNumber="226" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1374,2011]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="227" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1698,1723]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[352,540,1698,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">
Female 
<typeStatus box="[444,540,1698,1723]" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
(from Parque Estadual de Ilhabela, 
<collectionCode box="[949,1008,1699,1723]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/23qr-v2gj" name="Instituto Biologico de Sao Paulo" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">IBSP</collectionCode>
209896). Total length 3.30. Carapace length 0.88, width 0.73. Clypeus height 0.14. Sternum length 0.78, width 0.62. Abdomen length 2.18, width 2.18, height 1.97. Leg formula IV/I/II/III; segment length (I/II/III/IV): femora 1.91/1.40/1.02/1.95; patellae+tibiae 2.22/ 1.34/1.05/2.31; metatarsi+tarsi 2.94/1.95/1.61/3.12; total 7.07/4.70/3.69/7.39. Carapace orange-brown, semicircular, almost half the width of abdomen, cephalic region narrow, about half width of carapace (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1424,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 28" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[159,1403,193,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[159,1403,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 28. Body, dorsal view. Chrosiothes murici new species: 24, Male, 25, Female. Chrosiothes decorus new species: 26, Female. Chrosiothes una new species: 27, Female. Chrosiothes venturosus Marques &amp; Buckup, 1997: 28, Female. Scale bars, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002476/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae same color of carapace. Sternum lighter than carapace with darkened edges. AME, ALE and PLE with same diameter while PME are bigger. Legs with same color as the carapace. Abdomen oval, dorsum and venter yellow with irregular brown marks (
<figureCitation box="[567,654,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 28" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[159,1403,193,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[159,1403,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 28. Body, dorsal view. Chrosiothes murici new species: 24, Male, 25, Female. Chrosiothes decorus new species: 26, Female. Chrosiothes una new species: 27, Female. Chrosiothes venturosus Marques &amp; Buckup, 1997: 28, Female. Scale bars, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002476/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Dorsally without tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[994,1080,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 28" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[159,1403,193,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[159,1403,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 28. Body, dorsal view. Chrosiothes murici new species: 24, Male, 25, Female. Chrosiothes decorus new species: 26, Female. Chrosiothes una new species: 27, Female. Chrosiothes venturosus Marques &amp; Buckup, 1997: 28, Female. Scale bars, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002476/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Spinnerets yellow. Epigynum with a slightly sclerotized plate, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[713,795,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[162,1394,340,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1416,323,1258]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrosiothes decorus new species: Female: 13, Epigynum, ventral, 14, Internal genitalia, dorsal, clarified. Chrosiothes una new species: Female: 15, Epigynum, ventral. Scale bars, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002470/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) with a ventral subcircular depression (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1327,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[162,1394,340,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1416,323,1258]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrosiothes decorus new species: Female: 13, Epigynum, ventral, 14, Internal genitalia, dorsal, clarified. Chrosiothes una new species: Female: 15, Epigynum, ventral. Scale bars, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002470/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="226">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Internal genital with oval spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[516,600,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[162,1394,340,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1416,323,1258]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrosiothes decorus new species: Female: 13, Epigynum, ventral, 14, Internal genitalia, dorsal, clarified. Chrosiothes una new species: Female: 15, Epigynum, ventral. Scale bars, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002470/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); fertilization ducts shorts, uncoiled and copulatory ducts long and coiled, over the spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[416,500,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[162,1394,340,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1416,323,1258]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 15. Chrosiothes decorus new species: Female: 13, Epigynum, ventral, 14, Internal genitalia, dorsal, clarified. Chrosiothes una new species: Female: 15, Epigynum, ventral. Scale bars, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002470/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,389,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="227">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
